 outlets.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/chart-beat/7669133/billboard-genre-album-charts-consumption-streams-track-sales|title=Billboard's Genre Album Charts Will Now Incorporate Streams & Track Sales|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|date=January 26, 2017|accessdate=April 6, 2020}}</ref>\n\n{{-}}\n==Chart history==\n[[File:LukeBryanApr10.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Luke Bryan|[[Luke Bryan]] spent seven weeks at number one in 2014, the most by any act.]]\n[[File:JohnnyCash1969.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Johnny Cash|''[[Out Among the Stars]]'' was a posthumous number one for [[Johnny Cash]].]]\n[[File:Blake_Shelton_at_the_CMA_Awards_2019.jpg|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Blake Shelton|[[Blake Shelton]]'s album ''[[Based om a True Story...]]'', which had originally topped the chart the previous year, returned to number one in August 2014.]]\n[[File:191125_Carrie_Underwood_at_the_2019_American_Music_Awards.png|thumb|right|upright|alt=Singer Carrie Underwood|[[Carrie Underwood]] ended the year at number one.]]\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n!scope=col|Issue date\n!scope=col|Title\n!scope=col|Artist(s)\n!scope=col class=unsortable|Ref.\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 4}}\n| rowspan=\"2\"| ''[[Blame It All on My Roots: Five Decades of Influences]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\"| {{sortname|Garth|Brooks}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-01-04/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 4, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=December 27, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 11}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/charts/2014-01-11/country-albums|title=Country Albums chart for January 11, 2014|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=January 3, 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|{{dts|January 18}}\n| ''[[Crash My Party]]''\n| {{sortname|Luke|Bryan}}\n| align=center|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/cha