{"title_page": "Ee Nagaraniki Emaindhi", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{infobox film\n| name           = Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi\n| image          = Ee_Nagaraniki_Emaindi.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]]\n| producer       = Suresh Babu\n| screenplay     = [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]]\n| story          = [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]]\n| starring       = {{Unbulleted list\n  | [[Abhinav Gomatam]]\n  | Sai Sushanth Reddy\n  | [[Vishwaksen Naidu]]\n  | Venkatesh Kakamanu\n  | Simran Choudhary\n  | [[Anisha Ambrose]] \n  | [[Vijay Deverakonda]]}}\n| music          = [[Vivek Sagar]]\n| cinematography = Niketh Bommireddy\n| editing        = Ravi Teja Girijala\n| studio         = Suresh Productions\n| distributor    = {{Unbulleted list\n  | [[Suresh Productions]]\n }}\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2018|06|29}}\n| runtime        = 140 minutes\n| language       = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|6|c}}\n| box office     = {{INRConvert|45|c}}\n\n}}\n'''''Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi''''' (English: What happened to this city?) is a 2018 Indian  [[Telugu cinema|Telugu language]] [[buddy comedy]] written and directed by [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]] and produced by Suresh Babu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt8490894/|title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi|date=28 June 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018|via=www.imdb.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706160359/https://www.imdb.com/title/tt8490894/|archivedate=6 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatimes.com\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi/movie-review/64785903.cms|title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi Movie Review {3.5/5}: A hilarious film which takes you on a roller coaster ride and brings you the unexpected|website=indiatimes.com|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701153144/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi/movie-review/64785903.cms|archivedate=1 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/kt-rama-rao-rana-daggubati-attend-ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-pre-release-event-see-pics/story-7nJn3LjVikLfVhZwGYKSBN.html|title=KT Rama Rao, Rana Daggubati attend Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi pre-release event. See pics|date=26 June 2018|website=hindustantimes.com|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626115728/https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/kt-rama-rao-rana-daggubati-attend-ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-pre-release-event-see-pics/story-7nJn3LjVikLfVhZwGYKSBN.html|archivedate=26 June 2018}}</ref> The film received positive reviews from the audience and a majority of the film critics and collected 15 crores at box office. It was declared an ''Above Average''.\n\n==Plot==\nVivek, Karthik, Kaushik, and Uppi are childhood friends who dream of a career in film making during their college days. But they eventually give up their plans and settle in other jobs. Vivek resigns his job and lives in isolation, still trying to get over his breakup, Karthik works as a manager to a club and plans on marrying his owner's daughter and settle in the US, Kaushik works as a dubbing artist and he wanted to become an actor and Uppi works as a wedding photographer. After a misfired bachelors' party, they all end up in [[Goa]]. Karthik loses the engagement ring and needs \u20b95 lakhs to buy a similar kind of one. So they decide to participate in Goa Short film festival for the prize money. Vivek doesn't agree to make a romantic comedy film but later agrees as they don't have an alternative. Karthik handles the cinematography, Uppi edits the film and Kaushik acts in it. Vivek couldn't get out of his past and gives a sad ending to the film, and later gives up on the project as he fears the negative feedback. At this process when vivek drunk and slept the remaining three wanted to change the sad ending at that moment the police men were patroling at that place thery were caught to police and were shifted to station. While editing the film vivek wake up's by seeing them he gets angry on them and shout's on karthik . Karthik realizes that he is losing everything else for the social status and calls off his marriage. Kaushik gets the confidence to act in films and Uppi becomes an editor. After working on a few short films, they start their first feature film, [[Pelli Choopulu]]. \n\n==Cast==\n\n* [[Vishwak Sen]] as Vivek (Psycho Vivek)\n* Sai Sushanth Reddy as Karthik\n* [[Gautham Menon]] as himself, Cameo Appearance\n*[[Abhinav Gomatam]] as Kaushik\n* Venkatesh Kakumanu as Upender/Uppi\n*[[Anisha Ambrose]] as Shirley\n* Simran Choudhary as Shilpa\n*[[Vijay Deverakonda]] as himself\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThis film has five songs composed by [[Vivek Sagar]] and Released By [[Aditya Music]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi - All Songs - Download or Listen Free - Saavn |url=https://www.saavn.com/album/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi/8IWji18W6qc_ |website=Saavn |accessdate=29 October 2018 |date=14 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Ee Nagaraniki Emaindhi\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = Vivek Sagar\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{film date|df=y|2018|6|14}}\n| recorded   = 2018\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length     = 23:09\n| label      = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer   = Vivek Sagar\n| prev_title = [[Sammohanam (2018 film)|Sammohanam]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline  = Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Aagi Aagi\n| length1 = 6:48\n| lyrics1 = Krishna Kanth\n| extra1 = [[Anurag Kulkarni]], [[Manisha Eerabathini]]\n| title2 = Collegee Agelona\n| length2 = 2:38\n| lyrics2 = Kittu Vissapragada\n| extra2 = Wilson Herald\n| title3 = Swagatham Suswagatham\n| length3 = 2:02\n| lyrics3 = Cisco Chi\n| extra3 = Cisco Chi\n| title4 = Parada Jarupukoni\n| length4 = 4:32\n| lyrics4 = Kittu Vissapragada\n| extra4 = [[Vedala Hemachandra]]\n| title5 = Veediponidhi Okateley\n| length5 = 3:07\n| lyrics5 = Vivek Athreya\n| extra5 = [[Vivek Sagar]]\n| title6 = Maarey Kalaley\n| length6 = 4:02\n| lyrics6 = Vivek Athreya\n| extra6 = [[Sooraj Santhosh]]\n| total_length = 23:09\n}}\n\n== Release ==\n''Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi'' was released worldwide on 28 June 2018.\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nThe film has collected $98,136 from the premiere shows in USA held on Thursday night. On Day 1 on Friday, the film has collected $81,127.The total US box office collection was $179,263.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-07-01/Ee-Nagaraniki-Emaindi-Latest-Collections-Report/394172|title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi Latest Collections Report|website=The Hans India|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703133329/http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-07-01/Ee-Nagaraniki-Emaindi-Latest-Collections-Report/394172|archivedate=3 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-box-office-collections-tharun-bhasckers-second-feature-film-rakes-in-179263-gross-in-the-us/articleshow/64804636.cms|title='Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi' box office collections: Tharun Bhascker's second feature film rakes in $179,263 gross in the US - Times of India|website=indiatimes.com|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706160358/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-box-office-collections-tharun-bhasckers-second-feature-film-rakes-in-179263-gross-in-the-us/articleshow/64804636.cms|archivedate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical reception ===\n''[[The Hindu]]'' praised the film and stated \"With Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi, Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam breaks the second-film jinx that hounds many filmmakers who\u2019ve delivered an impressive first film.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-review-tharun-bhasckers-second-outing-is-a-lot-of-fun/article24288994.ece|title='Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi' review: Four guys and a short film|first=Sangeetha Devi|last=Dundoo|date=29 June 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018|via=www.thehindu.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706160358/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-review-tharun-bhasckers-second-outing-is-a-lot-of-fun/article24288994.ece|archivedate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Times of India]]'' gave 3.5/5 rating and commented that: \"Make no mistake, Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi belongs to Tharun Bhascker. The filmmaker\u2019s flair for comedy once again shines through and his dialogues are terrific.\"<ref name=\"indiatimes.com\"/>\n\n123 Telugu gave 3.25/5 rating and wrote, \"With Ee Nagarainiki Emaindi, Tollywood steps into the buddy comedy genre which has been rarely explored. This movie has no great story but is filled with a lot of fun and precious moments which a group of buddies share in real life.\"<ref>https://www.123telugu.com/reviews/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-telugu-movie-review.html</ref>\n\nThe Hans India gave 3/5 rating and wrote, \"...is one of the best youthful entertainers in the recent times. On the whole, the film is enjoyable entirely and even makes us emotional in parts.\"<ref>http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-06-29/Ee-Nagaraniki-Emaindi-Review--Rating-35/393559</ref>\n\nIdlebrain gave 3/5 rating and wrote, \"...is a buddy comedy that has good moments and a slow second half!\"<ref>http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/eenagaranikiemaindi.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8490894}}\n\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Telangana]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s buddy comedy films]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=March 2019}}\n{{infobox film\n| name           = Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi\n| image          = Ee_Nagaraniki_Emaindi.jpg\n| caption        = Theatrical release poster\n| director       = [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]]\n| producer       = Suresh Babu\n| screenplay     = [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]]\n| story          = [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]]\n| starring       = {{Unbulleted list\n  | [[Abhinav Gomatam]]\n  | Sai Sushanth Reddy\n  | [[Vishwaksen Naidu]]\n  | Venkatesh Kakamanu\n  | Simran Choudhary\n  | [[Anisha Ambrose]] \n  | [[Vijay Deverakonda]]}}\n| music          = [[Vivek Sagar]]\n| cinematography = Niketh Bommireddy\n| editing        = Ravi Teja Girijala\n| studio         = Suresh Productions\n| distributor    = {{Unbulleted list\n  | [[Suresh Productions]]\n }}\n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|2018|06|29}}\n| runtime        = 140 minutes\n| language       = [[Telugu language|Telugu]]\n| budget         = {{INRConvert|6|c}}\n| box office     = {{INRConvert|45|c}}\n\n}}\n'''''Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi''''' (English: What happened to this city?) is a 2018 Indian  [[Telugu cinema|Telugu language]] [[buddy comedy]] written and directed by [[Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam]] and produced by Suresh Babu.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt8490894/|title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi|date=28 June 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018|via=www.imdb.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706160359/https://www.imdb.com/title/tt8490894/|archivedate=6 July 2018}}</ref><ref name=\"indiatimes.com\">{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi/movie-review/64785903.cms|title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi Movie Review {3.5/5}: A hilarious film which takes you on a roller coaster ride and brings you the unexpected|website=indiatimes.com|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180701153144/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movie-reviews/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi/movie-review/64785903.cms|archivedate=1 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/kt-rama-rao-rana-daggubati-attend-ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-pre-release-event-see-pics/story-7nJn3LjVikLfVhZwGYKSBN.html|title=KT Rama Rao, Rana Daggubati attend Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi pre-release event. See pics|date=26 June 2018|website=hindustantimes.com|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180626115728/https://www.hindustantimes.com/regional-movies/kt-rama-rao-rana-daggubati-attend-ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-pre-release-event-see-pics/story-7nJn3LjVikLfVhZwGYKSBN.html|archivedate=26 June 2018}}</ref> The film received positive reviews from the audience and a majority of the film critics and collected 15 crores at box office. It was declared an ''Above Average''.\n\n==Plot==\nVivek, Karthik, Kaushik, and Uppi are childhood friends who dream of a career in film making during their college days. But they eventually give up their plans and settle in other jobs. Vivek resigns his job and lives in isolation, still trying to get over his breakup, Karthik works as a manager to a club and plans on marrying his owner's daughter and settle in the US, Kaushik works as a dubbing artist and he wanted to become an actor and Uppi works as a wedding photographer. After a misfired bachelors' party, they all end up in [[Goa]]. Karthik loses the engagement ring and needs \u20b95 lakhs to buy a similar kind of one. So they decide to participate in Goa Short film festival for the prize money. Vivek doesn't agree to make a romantic comedy film but later agrees as they don't have an alternative. Karthik handles the cinematography, Uppi edits the film and Kaushik acts in it. Vivek couldn't get out of his past and gives a sad ending to the film, and later gives up on the project as he fears the negative feedback. At this process when vivek drunk and slept the remaning three wanted to change the sad ending at that moment the police men were patroling at that place thery were caught to police and were shifted to station. While editing the film vivek wake up's by seeing them he gets angry on them and shout's on karthik . Karthik realizes that he is losing everything else for the social status and calls off his marriage. Kaushik gets the confidence to act in films and Uppi becomes an editor. After working on a few short films, they start their first feature film, [[Pelli Choopulu]]. \n\n==Cast==\n\n* [[Vishwak Sen]] as Vivek (Psycho Vivek)\n* Sai Sushanth Reddy as Karthik\n* [[Gautham Menon]] as himself, Cameo Appearance\n*[[Abhinav Gomatam]] as Kaushik\n* Venkatesh Kakumanu as Upender/Uppi\n*[[Anisha Ambrose]] as Shirley\n* Simran Choudhary as Shilpa\n*[[Vijay Deverakonda]] as himself\n\n==Soundtrack==\nThis film has five songs composed by [[Vivek Sagar]] and Released By [[Aditya Music]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi - All Songs - Download or Listen Free - Saavn |url=https://www.saavn.com/album/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi/8IWji18W6qc_ |website=Saavn |accessdate=29 October 2018 |date=14 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Ee Nagaraniki Emaindhi\n| type       = [[Soundtrack]]\n| artist     = Vivek Sagar\n| cover      =\n| alt        =\n| released   = {{film date|df=y|2018|6|14}}\n| recorded   = 2018\n| venue      =\n| studio     =\n| genre      = [[Soundtrack]]\n| length     = 23:09\n| label      = [[Aditya Music]]\n| producer   = Vivek Sagar\n| prev_title = [[Sammohanam (2018 film)|Sammohanam]]\n| prev_year  = 2018\n| next_title = \n| next_year  = \n}}\n{{track listing\n| headline  = Track listing\n| extra_column = Singer(s)\n| title1 = Aagi Aagi\n| length1 = 6:48\n| lyrics1 = Krishna Kanth\n| extra1 = [[Anurag Kulkarni]], [[Manisha Eerabathini]]\n| title2 = Collegee Agelona\n| length2 = 2:38\n| lyrics2 = Kittu Vissapragada\n| extra2 = Wilson Herald\n| title3 = Swagatham Suswagatham\n| length3 = 2:02\n| lyrics3 = Cisco Chi\n| extra3 = Cisco Chi\n| title4 = Parada Jarupukoni\n| length4 = 4:32\n| lyrics4 = Kittu Vissapragada\n| extra4 = [[Vedala Hemachandra]]\n| title5 = Veediponidhi Okateley\n| length5 = 3:07\n| lyrics5 = Vivek Athreya\n| extra5 = [[Vivek Sagar]]\n| title6 = Maarey Kalaley\n| length6 = 4:02\n| lyrics6 = Vivek Athreya\n| extra6 = [[Sooraj Santhosh]]\n| total_length = 23:09\n}}\n\n== Release ==\n''Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi'' was released worldwide on 28 June 2018.\n\n==Reception==\n===Box office===\nThe film has collected $98,136 from the premiere shows in USA held on Thursday night. On Day 1 on Friday, the film has collected $81,127.The total US box office collection was $179,263.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-07-01/Ee-Nagaraniki-Emaindi-Latest-Collections-Report/394172|title=Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi Latest Collections Report|website=The Hans India|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180703133329/http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-07-01/Ee-Nagaraniki-Emaindi-Latest-Collections-Report/394172|archivedate=3 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-box-office-collections-tharun-bhasckers-second-feature-film-rakes-in-179263-gross-in-the-us/articleshow/64804636.cms|title='Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi' box office collections: Tharun Bhascker's second feature film rakes in $179,263 gross in the US - Times of India|website=indiatimes.com|accessdate=6 July 2018|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706160358/https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/telugu/movies/box-office/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-box-office-collections-tharun-bhasckers-second-feature-film-rakes-in-179263-gross-in-the-us/articleshow/64804636.cms|archivedate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n=== Critical reception ===\n''[[The Hindu]]'' praised the film and stated \"With Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi, Tharun Bhascker Dhaassyam breaks the second-film jinx that hounds many filmmakers who\u2019ve delivered an impressive first film.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-review-tharun-bhasckers-second-outing-is-a-lot-of-fun/article24288994.ece|title='Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi' review: Four guys and a short film|first=Sangeetha Devi|last=Dundoo|date=29 June 2018|accessdate=6 July 2018|via=www.thehindu.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180706160358/https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/movies/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-review-tharun-bhasckers-second-outing-is-a-lot-of-fun/article24288994.ece|archivedate=6 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n''[[The Times of India]]'' gave 3.5/5 rating and commented that: \"Make no mistake, Ee Nagaraniki Emaindi belongs to Tharun Bhascker. The filmmaker\u2019s flair for comedy once again shines through and his dialogues are terrific.\"<ref name=\"indiatimes.com\"/>\n\n123 Telugu gave 3.25/5 rating and wrote, \"With Ee Nagarainiki Emaindi, Tollywood steps into the buddy comedy genre which has been rarely explored. This movie has no great story but is filled with a lot of fun and precious moments which a group of buddies share in real life.\"<ref>https://www.123telugu.com/reviews/ee-nagaraniki-emaindi-telugu-movie-review.html</ref>\n\nThe Hans India gave 3/5 rating and wrote, \"...is one of the best youthful entertainers in the recent times. On the whole, the film is enjoyable entirely and even makes us emotional in parts.\"<ref>http://www.thehansindia.com/posts/index/Tollywood/2018-06-29/Ee-Nagaraniki-Emaindi-Review--Rating-35/393559</ref>\n\nIdlebrain gave 3/5 rating and wrote, \"...is a buddy comedy that has good moments and a slow second half!\"<ref>http://www.idlebrain.com/movie/archive/eenagaranikiemaindi.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|8490894}}\n\n[[Category:2018 films]]\n[[Category:2010s Telugu-language films]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Telangana]]\n[[Category:Indian films]]\n[[Category:Indian buddy comedy films]]\n[[Category:2010s buddy comedy films]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Sp", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ee_Nagaraniki_Emaindhi"}
